						<tr>
							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">* You can make a hotkey macro to open all bags at once, the command is /togglebags
<br />

<br />
* The command to toggle your helmet as visible/invisible is /Showhood
<br />

<br />
* Set auto-run to your mouse wheel, makes it a simple click to run away and you can rotate camera to see what's chasing you.
<br />

<br />
* If you are shopping at a merchant, and accidentally buy something..you can sell it back at the same price --as long as you have not closed the merchant window
<br />

<br />
* To enable lotto as the default loot option for all groups you start, change the corresponding item in the options menu under group options
<br />

<br />
* Which tradeskill book recipies you have read can be viewed by clicking the EQ2 button and going to recipies. Your Recipie window will appear. At the top is a button labeled "EDIT." Hit this button and the Recipe window will change. There will be one big window with a scroll down bar on the far right which will contain three smaller windows that each will have a scroll down bar. Use the big scroll down bar on the far right to view the last window. This window displays the titles of all recipe books that that you have scribed. They are listed in the order you scribed them, and are not in alphabetical order. Helpful for determining if you need that rare book listed on the broker or if you already have it.
<br />

<br />
*You can select yourself and groupmates by pressing the F1-F6 keys. F1 is you and F6 would be the last member in your group. This is very helpful for assists and heals.
<br />

<br />
* Armor that's attunable must be attuned before it will give you any benefits.
<br />

<br />
* Try opening more chat windows and seperating combat, chat, game messages, etc.<br />_________________<br />- Terras.  Swashbuckler on Lucan Dlere server.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
