						<tr>
							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Awesome info! I always wondered what the heck those distressed merchants were for. The /mood command changes your facial expression which is fun.
<br />

<br />
Let me just add two things to the list.
<br />

<br />
To use multiple commands in a macro, you need to use /: at the beginning of the macro. Do not use / for commands within the macro, following the initial /:. Then separate each command by a space and ;. E.G. "/: ; useability Pathfinding ; gsay Casting Pathfinding".
<br />

<br />
To interrupt your own Combat Arts, use /sit. E.G. while casting Escape I may want to cancel it and can do so by typing /sit or using a hotkey for /sit, or simply pressing CTRL S.
<br />

<br />
(Moving forward or engaging attack automatically causes you to stand, /stand also works but why bother).
<br />

<br />
Edit: Deleted conflicting hotkey commands.<br />_________________<br />Jaedyn 48 Swashbuckler / 39 Provisioner
<br />
Grimol 26 Bruiser</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Jaedyn on Mon Dec 06, 2004 10:39 am; edited 3 times in total</span></td>
