What Shift does for me is select the numbered hotbar displayed in the primary's window.  Example: Set as my primary I have Hotbar 1, and I only need hit 1 - 9, - and = to activate the icon listed.  Set as my secondary I have icons needing ALT to activate. Set as my tertiary I have icons needing CTRL to activate.  When I hit &lt;SHIFT&gt; 4, for example, the fourth hotbar (out of ten? Twelve?) shows up in the primary window and I can activate those by pressing the corresponding number.<br />_________________<br />Stabbb Shadowalker
